parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls when coming to a stop
the vehicle shudders
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle loses motive power
and warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage
the vehicle shudders
the engine revs unexpectedly
the vehicle loses motive power
and warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the valve body can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission malfunctions
the vehicle shudders
the engine revs unexpectedly
the vehicle loses motive power
and warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cradle or frame can cause the vehicle to lose structural integrity, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine cradle or frame collapses
the vehicle swerves or pulls to one side
and the brakes malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine overheats
the radiator leaks
and warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent failure of headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Low beam headlights burn out frequently
sometimes simultaneously
with an average lifespan of 3-6 months. The headlights may not turn on
or may turn off while driving. In some cases
the high beams work
but the low beams do not.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical issues in the lighting system can cause a fire hazard, and the frequent failure of lights can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The lights may not turn on
or may turn off while driving. The headlights
brake lights
and other exterior lights may burn out frequently. In some cases
the lights may flicker or malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor design of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights do not provide sufficient illumination
with a noticeable line of darkness on the road. The low beams may not come on during the day
and the high beams may be the only reliable source of light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall has led to a significant delay in repair, leaving vehicle owners at risk of injury or death due to faulty airbags. The delay has also caused inconvenience and frustration among owners.
symptoms: Delayed repair
unavailability of parts
lack of communication from dealerships and manufacturers
and inability to use front passenger seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in an accident
resulting in injury or potential risk of injury.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and airbag system can lead to loss of control of the vehicle, resulting in accidents and potential injury or death.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration
loss of control
and failure of airbags to deploy.
